/wordpress.org/extend/plugins/dsero-anti-adblock-for-google-adsense/"><strong>dSero Anti AdBlock for Google AdSense</strong></a> outsmarts AdBlock extensions and keeps presenting your ads to your site visitors.</p>\n<p><a href="http://w-shadow.com/blog/2012/07/25/error-log-monitor-plugin/"><strong>Error Log Monitor</strong></a> adds a Dashboard widget that displays the latest messages from the PHP error log.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/paltip-plug-in/"><strong>PalTip</strong></a> locates the links that you have included in your post, then automatically replaces the original link with a new PalTip affiliate link.</p>\n<h3>Updated plugins</h3>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/comment-moderation-e-mail-to-post-author/"><strong>Comment Moderation E-mail only to Post Author</strong></a> sends the comment moderation notification only to the post author and no longer to the main site admin e-mail address too.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/highlight-search-terms/"><strong>Highlight Search Terms</strong></a> is a very lightweight jQuery script that wraps search terms in an HTML5 mark tag when the referrer is a search engine or within WordPress search results.</p>\n<p><a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/skype-online-status/"><strong>Skype Online Status</strong></a> allows you to add one or multiple, highly customizable and accessible Skype buttons to your site.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~4/7HsDZmtrlqA" height="1" width="1" />";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 01 Aug 2012 14:00:54 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"James";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:43:"Joseph: WordPress Core Contributor Handbook";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"https://josephscott.org/?p=6227";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"http://josephscott.org/archives/2012/07/wordpress-core-contributor-handbook/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:558:"<p>If you&#8217;ve ever asked &#8220;How can I contribute to WordPress?&#8221; then go check out the <a href="http://make.wordpress.org/core/handbook/">WordPress Core Contributor Handbook</a>.  While still early in development (you&#8217;ll see that some sections are just a stub list of topics that need to be covered) it is already worth reading if you are interested in how WordPress development works.</p>\n<p>A call been put out for someone to <a href="http://make.wordpress.org/core/2012/07/28/looking-for-a-lead/">lead the work on the handbook</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 31 Jul 2012 15:16:53 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Joseph Scott";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:10;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:13:"\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n	\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a