(107, 1, '2011-12-19 13:51:55', '2011-12-19 13:51:55', '<!--:vi--><h5><strong></strong>Những lý do nên có website\r\nAre you wondering if your business or organization really needs a website? Here are some reasons why a website is a great idea.<!--:--><!--:en--><h5><strong></strong>Reasons to Have a Website\r\nAre you wondering if your business or organization really needs a website? Here are some reasons why a website is a great idea.\r\nThe Internet provides equal access whether you are a small business or a Fortune 500 firm, therefore, it tends to "level the playing field."\r\nAs more and more businesses and organizations get online, those who don''t will increasingly be putting themselves at a competitive disadvantage.\r\nThe cost of a website is nominal when compared to the costs associated with traditional advertising methods such as direct mail, newspaper or magazine ads, radio, and television.\r\nWebsites offer the opportunity to provide your customers with up-to-date information when they need it and allow you the freedom to change your products, services, and information in a timely manner.\r\nYou can give your customers an extra incentive to visit your store or purchase from your website by providing them with coupons and information about sales directly on your website.\r\nAllows you to leverage your advertising dollars by displaying your Web address in other forms of advertising media. There is a limited amount of information that can be stuffed into expensive radio, TV, or print ads. Display your Web address to direct potential customers to your website where you can offer enough information to make the sale.\r\nYour website is a great place to publish your own list of "Frequently Asked Questions." Well thought out questions and answers, in as much detail as you like and exactly as you''d like it stated, can provide your customers with immediate assistance regarding their question while reducing the number of calls to your customer service staff.\r\nVi